Former Executive Chairman of Udu Local Government Council of Delta State, Hon Raymond Edijala has described the victory of Alhaji Atiku Abubakar as the presidential candidate and Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori as the gubernatorial candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in Delta State for the 2023 general election as evidence of God’s love for Nigeria., He stated this while congratulating both elder statemen for presenting themselves as agents of the real change Nigeria has been praying for, stressing that with Atiku as President and Oborevwori as Governor, Nigerians and Deltans will witness accelerated development in the coming dispensation. Addressing newsmen on the outcome of the PDP primary elections across Nigeria, Hon Edijala expressed immense pleasure with the peaceful conduct of the primaries, noting that PDP was primed to take over the reign of governance of the country in a unique, transparently organized and unprecedented air of democratic sobriety towards taking Nigeria out of the woods and placing the country on the path of economic recovery and political stability. -Advertisement- Hon Edijala noted “we are men and we don’t see the way God sees that’s why the much talk about the emergence of Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori as the gubernatorial candidate of the PDP. ”I assure our people that Delta state is bound to keep the pace of the democratic and infrastructural revolution initiated by Governor Ifeanyi Okowa and Oborevwori as governor will do more to keep the legacy of hard work, excellent performance and unequalled socio-economic prosperity for all Deltans.” He also sent words of unmistakable congratulations to other winners of the PDP primaries including Senator Ighoyota Amori, Delta Central senatorial candidate and Chief Jite Brown, House of Assembly candidate for Udu constituency for their victories in their respective primary elections, noting that with these men in the ballot in 2023, victory was sure for the party. Hon Edijala, an Executive Assistant to the governor of Delta State, expressed immense joy with the outcome of the elections, adding that PDP was better organized, united and more committed to providing a better alternative to the present and failed APC administration which, he said, has crippled the country beyond recognition. He added that with the complete breakdown of the security architecture of the country in the hands of the APC-led federal government, it will take experienced hands like Alhaji Atiku Abubakar to salvage the situation. POLL He congratulated the PDP family across Nigeria for standing for what is right by supporting Atiku Abubakar to victory, adding that all PDP candidates must be supported to victory so as to return our country to better days of revamped economy, the industrial revolution, peace and security and welfare for the citizens. Edijala noted that with Sheriff Oborevwori as governor of Delta State, Deltans will experience more and improved economic prosperity that will consolidate on the gains of the governor Okowa’s administration. “This message cannot end without appreciating the Governor of Delta state HE Sen Dr Arthur Ifeanyi Okowa for working tirelessly for the emergence of Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori and Sen Ighoyota Amori as well as Chief Jite Brown respectively. May God bless you and your heart desires for next level to be achieved in Jesus name amen”, he added.